name: CSSCounterStyleRule
description: The CSSCounterStyleRule interface represents an @counter-style at-rule.

members.name: CSSCounterStyleRule.name
members.description: Is a DOMString object that contains the serialization of the <counter-style-name> defined for the associated rule.

members.name: CSSCounterStyleRule.system
members.description: Is a DOMString object that contains the serialization of the system descriptor defined for the associated rule. If the descriptor was not specified in the associated rule, the attribute returns an empty string.

members.name: CSSCounterStyleRule.symbols
members.description: Is a DOMString object that contains the serialization of the symbols descriptor defined for the associated rule. If the descriptor was not specified in the associated rule, the attribute returns an empty string.

members.name: CSSCounterStyleRule.additiveSymbols
members.description: Is a DOMString object that contains the serialization of the additive-symbols descriptor defined for the associated rule. If the descriptor was not specified in the associated rule, the attribute returns an empty string.

members.name: CSSCounterStyleRule.negative
members.description: Is a DOMString object that contains the serialization of the negative descriptor defined for the associated rule. If the descriptor was not specified in the associated rule, the attribute returns an empty string.
